In terms of wetland hydrogeomorphic type, depression wetlands are the most threatened (24% of types threatened), followed by floodplains (17% of types threatened) and unchannelled valley-bottom wetlands (17% of types threatened), and seep wetland types (15% of types threatened) considered Threatened. Approximately 14% of depression wetland types and 19% of depression wetland extent is considered to be Critically Endangered, while 2% of seep wetland types, 1% of unchannelled valley-bottom wetland types and no floodplain types are considered Critically Endangered. <!-- add some dscription of this big difference in threat status for the different hgm zones, alignment with farming or mountains whatevewr ) -->

